OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be a cloudy day with
OL,6,Frain spreading eastwards across all
OL,7,Fparts, but dry in the east in the
OL,8,Fmorning. Mild in the east.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FIt will be cloudy through the
OL,11,Fevening with rain slowly spreading
OL,12,Feast, Rain turning to snow on the
OL,13,Fhills before clearing overnight, which
OL,14,Fmay allow some frost to develop.
OL,15,
OL,16,CFriday:FA cold and quite cloudy start
OL,17,Fwith perhaps the odd spot of rain over
OL,18,FFife. Otherwise dry with increasingly
OL,19,Fbright or sunny spells, but feeling
OL,20,Fcooler than recent days.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
